			<div id="s-lg-content-33974419" class="  clearfix">
				<p><strong><span class="h3">Features</span></strong><br /> <br /> <span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">&bull; Batch scan 50mm x 50mm mounted slides<br /> &bull; 48-bit, 5000 x 5000 dpi optical resolution<br /> &bull; Magic Touch/Auto Color/DNR or dust and scratch removal, color reconstruction, &nbsp; &nbsp;<br /> &nbsp; and grain equalization and management.<br /> &bull; USB 2.0</span></span></p>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Efficient Batch Scanning</strong> With the included slide magazine, the PowerSlide 5000 is capable of<br /> non-stop scanning up to 50 slides at a time. Single slides can also be scanned easily as well.</span></span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;</span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Superior Image Quality</strong> With advanced 5000dpi optical resolution, 48-bit data conversion,<br /> &nbsp;Dmax 3.8 dynamic range, PowerSlide5000 captures and digitizes a crisp and vivid image<br /> from the slide. ( Includes our patented Magic Touch dust and scratch removal technology)</span></span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;</span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Convenient Interface</strong> Equipped with USB 2.0 port, the most popular computer interface,<br /> &nbsp;PowerSlide 5000 offers you the benefit of versatility and fast performance.</span></span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;</span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Quick Slide Viewer </strong>The PowerSlide 5000 has built-in a mini light panel which allows you<br /> to conveniently view the slide image before scanning. Just rest the slide in the viewer and press down slightly (left).<br /></span></span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></span></div>
<div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></span></span></div>
